-It is very often that attackers breaches in a network just because of misconfiguration vulnerabilities (someone just forgot to secure something obvious similar as someone who forgets to close the door behind him).
It is more common with cloud
-Unsecured admin account is also a often used vulnerabilities (weak password).
-Insecure protocols: some protocols are not encrypted such as Telnet, FTP, SMTP, IMAP, and others which poses a risk. It is better to use secured protocols when possible such as SSH, SFTP, IMAPS, etc.
-Important to always change the default configurations (username, passwords) because some tools such as Mirai botnet as used and have data stored about all the software and devices default configurations.
-Open ports and services: important to limit their access.
